# hood.markets design engineering

Reference: [emilkowalski/skills](https://github.com/emilkowalski/skills) · [animations.dev](https://animations.dev/)

## Tokens (use these — do not invent one-off values)

| Token | Use |
|-------|-----|
| `--duration-ui` (160ms) | Buttons, hovers, small feedback |
| `--duration-panel` (220ms) | Page enter, progress bars |
| `--ease-out` | Enters, hovers, press release |
| `--ease-in-out` | On-screen movement |
| `--card-bg`, `--card-border`, `--card-radius`, `--shadow-card` | `.lp-card`, `.tp-zone`, `.token-card`, explore media |
| `--radius-sm/md/lg` | 8 / 10 / 14px |

## Motion rules

1. **High-frequency UI** (explore hover, tab nav, sidebar): minimal motion — no large lifts.
2. **Never `ease-in`** for UI enters; use `--ease-out`.
3. **Never `transition: all`** — list exact properties.
4. **Buttons**: `:hover`, `:focus-visible` ring, `:active { transform: scale(0.97) }`.
5. **Page enters**: `.lp-page-enter` on route wrapper in `App.tsx` only — do not stack `lp-fade-in` on child pages.
6. **`prefers-reduced-motion`**: disable transforms, animations, and transitions (see `index.css`).

## Surfaces

- **Raised cards** (launch forms, profile lists, sidebar zones): `--card-*` + `--shadow-card`.
- **Token page zones**: flat editorial — transparent bg, `--border-soft` dividers only (`.token-page .tp-zone` override).
- Prefer **soft borders** (`--border-soft`) over heavy `--border` on marketing surfaces.

## Before shipping UI changes

- [ ] Primary buttons have press + focus states
- [ ] New colors use theme vars (no hardcoded `#1a1a1a` in explore)
- [ ] Animations under 300ms unless explanatory
- [ ] Reduced-motion block updated if adding new animations
